🖥️ Linux Pre & Post Checks Automation

This project provides an Ansible-based automation to:

✅ Collect detailed pre-checks from Linux servers before patching or changes.
✅ Collect post-checks after patching or changes for validation.
📄 Store all outputs in a structured report per server.

------------------------------------------------------------
📌 Overview
The playbook captures and records key system information from Linux servers, including:

🔹 Server Information
  • 🏷️ Hostname
  • 🖥️ System type (OS + architecture)
  • 🧩 Kernel version
  • 📀 OS release

🔹 System Health
  • ⏱️ Uptime
  • 🌀 GRUB bootloader configuration
  • ⚙️ Sysctl configuration

🔹 Storage Details
  • 📊 Filesystem count
  • 💾 Mounted filesystems
  • 📂 fstab configuration
  • 💽 Disk details (via fdisk)
  • 📦 LVM information (PVs, VGs, LVs)

🔹 Network Information
  • 🌐 Network interface details (ifconfig -a)
  • 🛣️ Routing details (netstat -rn)

------------------------------------------------------------
⚙️ Prerequisites

🖥️ Control Node Requirements
  • 📌 Ansible v2.9+ installed
  • 🔑 SSH access to target Linux servers

📡 Managed Node Requirements
  • 🐍 Python installed
  • 👤 User with sudo privileges

📁 Inventory File Setup
Define target hosts under linux_servers:
    [linux_servers]
    server1 ansible_host=192.168.1.10
    server2 ansible_host=192.168.1.11

------------------------------------------------------------
▶️ How It Works

📝 Step 1: Gather Pre/Post Checks
Playbook: pre_post_checks.yml

• Connects to all servers in linux_servers group.
• Executes commands to capture system, storage, and network state.
• Registers command outputs into Ansible variables.

📝 Step 2: Save Reports
• Consolidates outputs into a formatted text file.
• Saves report on the control node in:
  /tmp/Pre-Post-Check-<hostname>.txt

------------------------------------------------------------
📄 Sample Format – Report Output

🖥️ Server Name: server1.example.com
🖥️ System Type: Linux x86_64
🧩 Kernel Version: 4.18.0-425.19.2.el8.x86_64
⏱️ System Uptime: 10:52:01 up 3 days,  4:21,  2 users,  load average: 0.15, 0.08, 0.05
📀 OS Release: Red Hat Enterprise Linux release 8.8 (Ootpa)
📊 Filesystem Count: 5
💾 Mounted Filesystems:
Filesystem     Type  Size  Used Avail Use% Mounted on
/dev/sda1      ext4   40G   20G   18G  52% /
...

------------------------------------------------------------
📤 Outputs

✅ Server information report stored as:
   /tmp/Pre-Post-Check-<hostname>.txt

✅ Consolidated details covering:
   • OS & Kernel
   • Uptime & GRUB settings
   • Filesystems, LVM, Disk details
   • Network interfaces & routing
